                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="441254" author="adilger" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2025 18:58:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For commands like &quot;ls&quot; they will default to printing the name, if it can be looked up, and print the number of the lookup fails.  &quot;ls -n&quot; will only print the number, for cases where that is important, or if the name lookup is slow/broken (eg. using a network LDAP database that is overloaded or offline).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt; &quot;lfs quota&quot; is doing the same (prefer name, fall back to number).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
